# Plan: Convert Cursor Skills to Claude Code Skills & Agents

## Context
The user has 7 skill definitions in `.cursor/skills/` (Cursor editor format). They want these transferred to Claude Code's user-scope `~/.claude/` directory. Each skill should be classified as either a **skill** (contextual guidance in conversation) or a **sub-agent** (autonomous sub-process). Playwright is excluded (already available).

## Classification Rationale

| Cursor Skill | → Claude Code | Why |
|---|---|---|
| **code-cleaner** | Agent | Autonomous iterative task — runs ruff/ty, fixes issues in a loop, returns summary. No user interaction needed during execution. |
| **code-onboarder** | Agent | Autonomous exploration + generation — explores repo, produces `system-architecture.md`. Self-contained output. |
| **docstring-numpy** | Agent | Autonomous batch conversion — iterates files, converts docstrings, returns summary. |
| **gh-fix-ci** | Agent | Autonomous investigation — inspects failing checks via `gh` CLI, analyzes logs, reports findings. Has a helper Python script. |
| **pr-description** | Skill | Interactive workflow — needs user context (branch, audience, PR type). Produces output inline in conversation. |
| **visual-explainer** | Skill | Creative guidance with templates/references — needs to stay in conversation for aesthetic choices and iteration. Complex supporting files. |
| **obsidian-cli** | Skill | Pure reference material — command syntax guide that augments conversation context when Obsidian work is happening. |

